{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Mrk|4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","chapter":4,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":1,"text":"Again he began to teach by the sea, and a very large crowd gathered around him. So he got into a boat on the sea and sat down, while the whole crowd was by the sea on the shore.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":2,"text":"He taught them many things in parables, and in his teaching he said to them,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":3,"text":"“Listen! Consider the sower who went out to sow.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":4,"text":"As he sowed, some seed fell along the path, and the birds came and devoured it.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":5,"text":"Other seed fell on rocky ground where it didn’t have much soil, and it grew up quickly, since the soil wasn’t deep.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":6,"text":"When the sun came up, it was scorched, and since it had no root, it withered away.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":7,"text":"Other seed fell among thorns, and the thorns came up and choked it, and it didn’t produce fruit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":8,"text":"Still other seed fell on good ground and it grew up, producing fruit that increased thirty, sixty, and a hundred times.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":9,"text":"Then he said, “Let anyone who has ears to hear listen.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":10,"text":"When he was alone, those around him with the Twelve asked him about the parables.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":11,"text":"He answered them, “The secret of the kingdom of God has been given to you, but to those outside, everything comes in parables","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":12,"text":"so that","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":13,"text":"Then he said to them, “Don’t you understand this parable? How then will you understand all of the parables?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":14,"text":"The sower sows the word.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":15,"text":"Some are like the word sown on the path. When they hear, immediately Satan comes and takes away the word sown in them.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":16,"text":"And others are like seed sown on rocky ground. When they hear the word, immediately they receive it with joy.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":17,"text":"But they have no root; they are short-lived. When distress or persecution comes because of the word, they immediately fall away.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":18,"text":"Others are like seed sown among thorns; these are the ones who hear the word,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":19,"text":"but the worries of this age, the deceitfulness of wealth, and the desires for other things enter in and choke the word, and it becomes unfruitful.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":20,"text":"And those like seed sown on good ground hear the word, welcome it, and produce fruit thirty, sixty, and a hundred times what was sown.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":21,"text":"He also said to them, “Is a lamp brought in to be put under a basket or under a bed? Isn’t it to be put on a lampstand?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":22,"text":"For there is nothing hidden that will not be revealed, and nothing concealed that will not be brought to light.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":23,"text":"If anyone has ears to hear, let him listen.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":24,"text":"And he said to them, “Pay attention to what you hear. By the measure you use, it will be measured to you —and more will be added to you.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":25,"text":"For whoever has, more will be given to him, and whoever does not have, even what he has will be taken away from him.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":26,"text":"“The kingdom of God is like this,” he said. “A man scatters seed on the ground.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":27,"text":"He sleeps and rises night and day; the seed sprouts and grows, although he doesn’t know how.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":28,"text":"The soil produces a crop by itself —first the blade, then the head, and then the full grain on the head.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":29,"text":"As soon as the crop is ready, he sends for the sickle, because the harvest has come.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":30,"text":"And he said, “With what can we compare the kingdom of God, or what parable can we use to describe it?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":31,"text":"It’s like a mustard seed that, when sown upon the soil, is the smallest of all the seeds on the ground.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:32","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":32,"text":"And when sown, it comes up and grows taller than all the garden plants, and produces large branches, so that the birds of the sky can nest in its shade.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:33","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":33,"text":"He was speaking the word to them with many parables like these, as they were able to understand.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:34","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":34,"text":"He did not speak to them without a parable. Privately, however, he explained everything to his own disciples.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:35","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":35,"text":"On that day, when evening had come, he told them, “Let’s cross over to the other side of the sea.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:36","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":36,"text":"So they left the crowd and took him along since he was in the boat. And other boats were with him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:37","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":37,"text":"A great windstorm arose, and the waves were breaking over the boat, so that the boat was already being swamped.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:38","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":38,"text":"He was in the stern, sleeping on the cushion. So they woke him up and said to him, “Teacher! Don’t you care that we’re going to die?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:39","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":39,"text":"He got up, rebuked the wind, and said to the sea, “Silence! Be still!” The wind ceased, and there was a great calm.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:40","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":40,"text":"Then he said to them, “Why are you afraid? Do you still have no faith?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:41","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","bookOrder":40,"chapter":4,"verse":41,"text":"And they were terrified and asked one another, “Who then is this? Even the wind and the sea obey him!”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Mrk","chapter":4,"paragraphStarts":[1,10,13,21,26,30,33,35,39,41],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Parable of the Sower"},{"beforeVerse":10,"text":"Why Jesus Used Parables"},{"beforeVerse":13,"text":"The Parable of the Sower Explained"},{"beforeVerse":21,"text":"Using Your Light"},{"beforeVerse":26,"text":"The Parable of the Growing Seed"},{"beforeVerse":30,"text":"The Parable of the Mustard Seed"},{"beforeVerse":33,"text":"Using Parables"},{"beforeVerse":35,"text":"Wind and Waves Obey Jesus"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Again "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 13:1–15","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 8:4–10","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" he began to teach "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 28:20","book":"Mat","chapter":28,"verse":20,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 4:2","book":"Act","chapter":4,"verse":2,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Tm 4:11","book":"2Ti","chapter":4,"verse":11,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"text","text":" by the sea, and a very large crowd gathered around him. So he got into a boat on the sea and sat down, while the whole crowd was by the sea on the shore. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 13:1–15","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":1},{"label":"Lk 8:4–10","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":4},{"label":"Mt 28:20","book":"Mat","chapter":28,"verse":20},{"label":"Ac 4:2","book":"Act","chapter":4,"verse":2},{"label":"2Tm 4:11","book":"2Ti","chapter":4,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He taught them many things in parables, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and in his teaching "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 11:18","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":18,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 2:42","book":"Act","chapter":2,"verse":42,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 17:19","book":"Act","chapter":17,"verse":19,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" he said to them, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 12:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1},{"label":"Mk 11:18","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":18},{"label":"Ac 2:42","book":"Act","chapter":2,"verse":42},{"label":"Ac 17:19","book":"Act","chapter":17,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“Listen! Consider the sower who went out to sow."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 6:7","book":"Gal","chapter":6,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gl 6:7","book":"Gal","chapter":6,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"As he sowed, some seed fell along the path,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 8:27","book":"Mrk","chapter":8,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the birds came and devoured"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 5:15","book":"Gal","chapter":5,"verse":15,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" it. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 8:27","book":"Mrk","chapter":8,"verse":27},{"label":"Gl 5:15","book":"Gal","chapter":5,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Other seed fell on rocky ground where it didn’t have much soil, and it grew up quickly,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 10:52","book":"Mrk","chapter":10,"verse":52,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" since the soil wasn’t deep. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 10:52","book":"Mrk","chapter":10,"verse":52}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When the sun came up, it was scorched, and since it had no root, it withered away."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 3:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":3,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 3:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":3,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Other seed fell among thorns, and the thorns came up and choked it, and it didn’t produce fruit. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Still other seed fell on good ground and it grew up, producing fruit that increased"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 2:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" thirty, sixty, and a hundred times.”"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 15:5","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":5,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 1:6","book":"Col","chapter":1,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Pt 2:2","book":"1Pe","chapter":2,"verse":2},{"label":"Jn 15:5","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":5},{"label":"Col 1:6","book":"Col","chapter":1,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then he said, “Let anyone who has ears to hear listen.”"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 6:9","book":"Isa","chapter":6,"verse":9,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jr 5:21","book":"Jer","chapter":5,"verse":21,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ezk 12:2","book":"Ezk","chapter":12,"verse":2,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 8:18","book":"Mrk","chapter":8,"verse":18,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 14:35","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":35,"letter":"e"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 6:9","book":"Isa","chapter":6,"verse":9},{"label":"Jr 5:21","book":"Jer","chapter":5,"verse":21},{"label":"Ezk 12:2","book":"Ezk","chapter":12,"verse":2},{"label":"Mk 8:18","book":"Mrk","chapter":8,"verse":18},{"label":"Lk 14:35","book":"Luk","chapter":14,"verse":35}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When he was alone, those around him with the Twelve "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 11:11","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" asked him about the parables. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 11:11","book":"Mrk","chapter":11,"verse":11},{"label":"Mk 12:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He answered them, “The secret"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 2:7","book":"1Co","chapter":2,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" of the kingdom of God"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 1:15","book":"Mrk","chapter":1,"verse":15,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" has been given to you, but to those outside,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:27","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":27,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" everything comes in parables "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Co 2:7","book":"1Co","chapter":2,"verse":7},{"label":"Mk 1:15","book":"Mrk","chapter":1,"verse":15},{"label":"Rm 9:27","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"so that"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 13:18–23","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 8:9–15","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":9,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" he said to them, “Don’t you understand this parable?"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 12:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" How then will you understand all of the parables? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mt 13:18–23","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":18},{"label":"Lk 8:9–15","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":9},{"label":"Mk 12:1","book":"Mrk","chapter":12,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The sower sows"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 6:7","book":"Gal","chapter":6,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" the word."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 16:20","book":"Mrk","chapter":16,"verse":20,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gl 6:7","book":"Gal","chapter":6,"verse":7},{"label":"Mk 16:20","book":"Mrk","chapter":16,"verse":20}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Some are like the word sown on the path."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 8:27","book":"Mrk","chapter":8,"verse":27,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" When they hear, immediately Satan"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 4:10","book":"Mat","chapter":4,"verse":10,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" comes and takes away the word"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:47","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":47,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" sown in them."},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Other mss read in their hearts"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 8:27","book":"Mrk","chapter":8,"verse":27},{"label":"Mt 4:10","book":"Mat","chapter":4,"verse":10},{"label":"Lk 6:47","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":47}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Other mss read in their hearts"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And others are like seed sown on rocky ground. When they hear the word, immediately they receive it with joy."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 5:43","book":"Jhn","chapter":5,"verse":43,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 15:11","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jn 5:43","book":"Jhn","chapter":5,"verse":43},{"label":"Jn 15:11","book":"Jhn","chapter":15,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But they have no root; they are short-lived. When distress"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 1:4","book":"2Co","chapter":1,"verse":4,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" or persecution comes because of the word, they immediately fall away."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 16:1","book":"Jhn","chapter":16,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Co 1:4","book":"2Co","chapter":1,"verse":4},{"label":"Jn 16:1","book":"Jhn","chapter":16,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Others are like seed sown among thorns; these are the ones who hear the word, "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"but the worries"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Pt 5:7","book":"1Pe","chapter":5,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" of this age,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 16:8","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":8,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Eph 1:21","book":"Eph","chapter":1,"verse":21,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" the deceitfulness"},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Or seduction"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 13:22","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":22,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" of wealth,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 13:22","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":22,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 8:14","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":14,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" and the desires"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 1:4","book":"2Pe","chapter":1,"verse":4,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Pt 2:10","book":"2Pe","chapter":2,"verse":10,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"text","text":" for other things enter in and choke the word, and it becomes unfruitful."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 1:13","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":13,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ti 3:14","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":14,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jd 1:12","book":"Jud","chapter":1,"verse":12,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Pt 5:7","book":"1Pe","chapter":5,"verse":7},{"label":"Lk 16:8","book":"Luk","chapter":16,"verse":8},{"label":"Eph 1:21","book":"Eph","chapter":1,"verse":21},{"label":"Mt 13:22","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":22},{"label":"Mt 13:22","book":"Mat","chapter":13,"verse":22},{"label":"Lk 8:14","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":14},{"label":"2Pt 1:4","book":"2Pe","chapter":1,"verse":4},{"label":"2Pt 2:10","book":"2Pe","chapter":2,"verse":10},{"label":"Rm 1:13","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":13},{"label":"Ti 3:14","book":"Tit","chapter":3,"verse":14},{"label":"Jd 1:12","book":"Jud","chapter":1,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[{"marker":2,"text":"Or seduction"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And those like seed sown on good ground hear the word,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 6:47","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":47,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" welcome it, and produce fruit"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Col 1:10","book":"Col","chapter":1,"verse":10,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" thirty, sixty, and a hundred times what was sown.”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 6:47","book":"Luk","chapter":6,"verse":47},{"label":"Col 1:10","book":"Col","chapter":1,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 8:16–18","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" also said to them, “Is a lamp brought in to be put under a basket or under a bed?"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 5:18","book":"Luk","chapter":5,"verse":18,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Isn’t it to be put on a lampstand?"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rv 1:12","book":"Rev","chapter":1,"verse":12,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 8:16–18","book":"Luk","chapter":8,"verse":16},{"label":"Lk 5:18","book":"Luk","chapter":5,"verse":18},{"label":"Rv 1:12","book":"Rev","chapter":1,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For there is nothing hidden that will not be revealed,"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 4:11","book":"2Co","chapter":4,"verse":11,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and nothing concealed that will not be brought to light. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Co 4:11","book":"2Co","chapter":4,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Mrk:4:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"If anyone has ears to hear, let him listen.”"},{"kind":"crossref","label":